<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17524] Camel loading of resources using ClassResolver API doesn&apos;t work in OSGi enviroments</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17524</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17116&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17116&lt;/a&gt; changed how resources were loaded in several components the problem being that now they don&apos;t use the classloader of the class making the resource calls in OSGi environments. Its a simple change to call the method&#160;loadResourceAsStream(String name, ClassLoader loader) and passing in the calling classes class loader instead of&#160;loadResourceAsStream(String name).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
