                            <comment id="17479916" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 21 Jan 2022 09:04:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are welcome to send a PR&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17479940" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 21 Jan 2022 09:26:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;camel-schematron fixed&lt;br/&gt;
camel-quartz already fixed&lt;br/&gt;
camel-jslt already fixed&lt;br/&gt;
camel-xmlsecurity fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17480280" author="ryeats" created="Fri, 21 Jan 2022 22:43:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I would have put up a PR right when i wrote the ticket but it took me a while to get my development environment working for camel and everything good to build. I checked your fix and it looks like you missed ClassPathURIResolver.java&#160; resource loading call so I went ahead and pushed an additional PR up with that fix and a couple other places that may have the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17480281" author="ryeats" created="Fri, 21 Jan 2022 22:44:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix that was originally applied did not fully resolve the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17480373" author="davsclaus" created="Sat, 22 Jan 2022 08:26:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We do not support all components in OSGi such as jbpm etc so they should not be changed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17480502" author="davsclaus" created="Sat, 22 Jan 2022 17:29:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ryan, thanks for the fixes. We had to rush this as we are building the 3.14.1 release later this weekend&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
